<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10273971>
    dc:description "Figure 8. Reconstructions of the clypeus shape and meso- and metathoracic morphology of the Early Cretaceous hydrophilid genera known in adult stage (three-dimensional structure of the mesoventrite not reconstructed). Alegorius gen. nov. (A, B); Cretoxenus gen. nov. (C, D); Hydroyixia gen. nov. (E, F). Head and thorax of the respective genus not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10273971/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

